{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Make domestic abuse workplace policies mandatory in England and Wales",
        "additional_details": "1 in 4 women & 1 in 6 men suffer from domestic abuse in their lifetime and domestic abuse costs businesses \u00a31.9 billion per year due to decreased productivity, time off work, lost wages and sick pay. 1 in 5 survivors take time off work due to abuse.\r\n\r\nA fifth of people meet their partner at work, and requiring employers to put in place policies to provide a supportive and safe workplace can help keep victims safe.\r\n \r\nEvery employer has a role to play including protection at work.",
        "background": "While guidance to help employers spot signs of domestic abuse is available, I feel that without a requirement that all employers have to put in place robust policies, much domestic abuse will continue to go unnoticed.",
